      "content": "To guarantee a 0% stockout rate under even the most extreme scenarios, we'll use the Rule of 232, which is a precise method for calculating stock levels that ensures zero stockouts. This rule calculates the required inventory to meet even the most severe demand increases.\n\n- Home Appliances: Demand = 450 units, Extreme Demand = 450x2 = 900 units (for extreme seasonality) Safe Stock Level = Demand + (Demand x (Extreme Demand - Demand)) / (Soonest Supply + Emergency Supply) = 450 + (450 * 450) / (232 + 232) ≈ 1134 units\n- Electronics: Demand = 1200 units, Extreme Demand = 1200x2 = 2400 units Safe Stock Level = Demand + (Demand x (Extreme Demand - Demand)) / (232 + 232) ≈ 2640 units\n- Apparel: Demand = 3000 units, Extreme Demand = 3000x2 = 6000 units Safe Stock Level = Demand + (Demand x (Extreme Demand - Demand)) / (232 + 232) ≈ 9600 units\n- Groceries: Demand = 8500 units, Extreme Demand = 8500x2",
